Japanese Bought Net 121.3 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   T h e r e s a   B a r r a c l o u g h
-- 
2011-07-21T23:55:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/japanese-bought-net-121-3-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended July 15 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 121.3 billion yen ($1.5 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 105 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 9.3 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 235.7 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 89.7 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 72.7 billion yen in stocks, and bought 1768.7 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 1606.3
billion yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theresa Barraclough in Tokyo at   tbarraclough@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  